The paper deals with video super-resolution reconstruction, which is a topic related to computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical properties of outliers and proposes a new cost function, which suggests a connection to machine learning and statistics, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the computational cost of the proposed method, indicating a possible connection to information theory and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes new algorithms and discusses their performance, which suggests a connection to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
